&lt;p&gt;This component implements infinite scrolling by continuously fetching more posts as the user reaches the bottom of the page. React Query manages pages internally and loads new data using &lt;code&gt;fetchNextPage()&lt;/code&gt;, while the &lt;code&gt;useEffect&lt;/code&gt; scroll listener detects when the user is near the bottom. Each fetched page gets appended to the existing feed, creating a seamless, continuous scrolling experience. As long as the backend reports &lt;code&gt;hasMore&lt;/code&gt;, the feed keeps expanding without any ‚ÄúNext‚Äù buttons.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is &lt;strong&gt;true infinite scroll&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî scroll triggers the fetch, React Query stacks the pages, and the UI grows dynamically.&lt;/p&gt;




